---

If the `ai-skills/` directory is empty or missing, initialize the submodule first: `git submodule update --init ai-skills`

When adding or modifying Kinetic Platform skills, make changes inside `ai-skills/` and submit a pull request to the `kineticdata/kinetic-platform-ai-skills` repository so all projects benefit from the update.

Apply the following patterns when building or modifying Kinetic front-end portals using @kineticdata/react and KineticLib.

@ai-skills/skills/front-end/bootstrap/SKILL.md
@ai-skills/skills/front-end/forms/SKILL.md
@ai-skills/skills/front-end/data-fetching/SKILL.md
@ai-skills/skills/front-end/mutations/SKILL.md
@ai-skills/skills/front-end/state/SKILL.md
